      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The race drops away very quickly outside the top few. MAX ROCK (9) ran on strongly to just miss last start over 2000m at Alice Springs. Doesn't win out of turn but this rates easier and looks hard to hold out. BOLLON (2) was an impressive winner last time over 1600m at this track, leading throughout and putting 7 lengths on his rivals. Will prove very tough to beat again. NO I'M NOT (4) finished fifth two runs back at this track then improved last time out to score by 0.8 lengths over 1300m at this track. First try at the trip but in form and looks a leading player. THE ALBION (7) showed good early speed and raced on the pace last start before fading to finish fourth behind the in-form Ankle Rolex over 1300m here. Great record at this course and distance and looks well weighted with the claim. JULY (6) has been thereabouts and can do better.",
